{"TopicId":204167,"ForumId":148,"TopicTitle":"Kerbal Space Progam 1.12.2 is live!","CreatedByName":"UomoCapra","CreatedById":167737,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-03T17:00:00Z","PageNum":4,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"mistergoblin","CreatedById":178658,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-06T13:11:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis isn\u0027t a shooter, none of the above applies\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakete","CreatedById":208801,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-06T14:26:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015333\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628233225\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161238\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Anth12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Anth12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLocking docking ports ONLY allows autostruts through, it was never made to fix the drift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep. Definitely an issue. Here\u0027s my bug report that I did for this on the 18th of July\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/28311\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/28311\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1.11 and all previous versions\u00A0crafts with docking ports and excluding robotics would\u003Cstrong\u003E snap back\u003C/strong\u003E into position on timewarp/reloading scene.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis doesn\u0027t happen in 1.12, the video in my bug report shows the test craft (with 1 docking port) \u003Cstrong\u003Egiving a little each time\u003C/strong\u003E timewarp is disengaged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn my opinion 1.12 is broken unless they give us at least a docking port variant that is using the old code. It confuses me why \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003Eare ignoring this issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love 1.12 \u003Cb\u003Eexcept\u003C/b\u003E\u00A0for the rotational docking ports causing drift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI really wonder why we only get silence on this topic. We already spotlighted this \u003Cu\u003Eshowstopper\u003C/u\u003E issue already in the 1.12.1 thread intensively. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022148725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Just Jim\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0... Can we please get a statement on this issue? Can we get a bugfix on this, as it prohibits any complex space structure (station/vessel) to last. Or are the complex-things-builders doomed to stay on 1.11.2 with all it\u0027s other bugs? Is this issue in the scope of the remaining bugfix team?\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EPlease communicate to us.\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-06T14:37:35Z\u0022 title=\u002208/06/2021 02:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 6, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Rakete\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-06T14:42:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015375\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628245131\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022serdan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, serdan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOpen source can have restrictive licensing. They could allow pull requests from fans while retaining full rights.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for competition, if they do a good job on the sequel it\u0027ll only be die hard fans who continue playing the original (and most of those will buy the sequel regardless).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re probably not going to do it, because corporations are gonna corporate, but the arguments against aren\u0027t nearly as strong as you\u0027d think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy point is that I can\u0027t see any commercial gains to be found for Take Two.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd as a commercial company they\u0027re obligated to seek the best economical solution for their owners.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Themisto","CreatedById":213478,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-06T15:28:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince the update i cant use my \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E properly anymore (from 1.12.1 savefile) in carrier modus.\u00A0 The Button is shown and some\u00A0 features work like stabilization, but other like maneuver or target\u00A0 arent even displayed. I wonder if anyone else have the same problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-06T16:06:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628259979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rakete\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Rakete said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI really wonder why we only get silence on this topic. We already spotlighted this \u003Cu\u003Eshowstopper\u003C/u\u003E issue already in the 1.12.1 thread intensively. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022148725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Just Jim\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0... Can we please get a statement on this issue? Can we get a bugfix on this, as it prohibits any complex space structure (station/vessel) to last. Or are the complex-things-builders doomed to stay on 1.11.2 with all it\u0027s other bugs? Is this issue in the scope of the remaining bugfix team?\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EPlease communicate to us.\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for logging this. We are aware of the issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakete","CreatedById":208801,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-06T16:55:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628265990\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for logging this. We are aware of the issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, than i will modify my question slightly: Will this issue be in focus for the next \u0022here and there when needed\u0022-minor-bugfix-update? This bug is unfortunately a major one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-06T21:58:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022148725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Just Jim\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0A work around with a old docking port variant (that uses the old code)\u00A0is all that is needed in my opinion for KSP 1.12 to be viable, this bypasses the drift that is a lot harder to fix.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-06T21:59:08Z\u0022 title=\u002208/06/2021 09:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 6, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EI already said this...nm\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T00:06:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015733\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628287083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161238\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Anth12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Anth12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022148725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Just Jim\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0A work around with a old docking port variant (that uses the old code)\u00A0is all that is needed in my opinion for KSP 1.12 to be viable, this bypasses the drift that is a lot harder to fix.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think there\u0027s another option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstead of changing an already deployed and in production code (the new DockingPort Module), I think a new (custom) module can fix the problem: Every time the craft goes on rails, the module would save the current attachment positions of its Part, and once the craft goes off rails, the module would restore these values. Additional benefit is you being able to patch this module on any needing part, and not only on Docking Ports - any similar glitch on any other\u00A0part\u00A0would be fixed with a new \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will give this a try this WeekEnd on KSP-Recall, let\u0027s see if I manage to pull this stunt.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T00:59:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m working on a mod to fix the docking port issue. Which works. So stay tuned will release it soon as I complete testing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T01:23:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628297968\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m working on a mod to fix the docking port issue. Which works. So stay tuned will release it soon as I complete testing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*should be stock...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJks.\u00A0 Thanks for doing this \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EPeace.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T03:18:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628297968\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m working on a mod to fix the docking port issue. Which works. So stay tuned will release it soon as I complete testing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for doing this, hopefully testing goes well, good luck!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RyanRising","CreatedById":79932,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T04:06:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628297968\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m working on a mod to fix the docking port issue. Which works. So stay tuned will release it soon as I complete testing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T05:42:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is a mod I\u0027ve created that will fix the stock docking port drift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsEmbed_finishedLoading\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6556196879\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/204248-112x-fix-stock-docking-nodes-7th-august-2021/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022overflow: hidden; height: 192px; max-width: 500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ENOTE: This fix ONLY works for docking ports that are LOCKED or Undocked!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIt will not fix docking ports that are unlocked and docked!!! So the bottom line is leave your docking ports LOCKED unless you are actively rotating them.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161238-anth12/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022161238\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161238-anth12/\u0022 id=\u0022ips_uid_7597_15\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Anth12\u003C/a\u003E for helping me test it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T05:48:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you so much\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for fixing this bug.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dok_377","CreatedById":171956,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T07:21:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf only the same could be done for the robotic drift as well.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T07:54:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am sure its not that simple. But you have peaked my interest \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171956-dok_377/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022171956\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171956-dok_377/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@dok_377\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me see if I can make the code for the docking port drift work for robotics even in a limited form\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dok_377","CreatedById":171956,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T07:58:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015931\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628322863\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161238\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Anth12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Anth12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am sure its not that simple. But you have peaked my interest \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171956-dok_377/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022171956\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171956-dok_377/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@dok_377\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me see if I can make the code for the docking port drift work for robotics even in a limited form\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere surely has to be a way. That one fix would literally change the whole game and improve it immensely.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T08:01:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRobotics are more complicated. I doubt it will work, but it will be fun to try\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakete","CreatedById":208801,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T08:15:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0thanks a lot for this, why not make it stock? I would guess, you can put it in 1.12.3 as Lead engineer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso: does the effects of the Mod also take affect on mod-dockingports like the ones from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s\u00A0packages (Restock, NF Launch Vehicles, NF Construction, etc?) or will they have to actively made compatible to use your docking port stabilizer?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T08:16:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy coding is limited to creating a mod that can display parts coordinates. How I make the ModuleManager hook into the code I am not sure yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T08:33:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015936\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628324117\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rakete\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Rakete said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0thanks a lot for this, why not make it stock? I would guess, you can put it in 1.12.3 as Lead engineer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso: does the effects of the Mod also take affect on mod-dockingports like the ones from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s\u00A0packages (Restock, NF Launch Vehicles, NF Construction, etc?) or will they have to actively made compatible to use your docking port stabilizer?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDepends on what module the mod uses. If it uses the stock module then yes. If it uses its own module then no.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nas for making it stock, you did read the opening post of this thread yeah?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628324178\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161238\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Anth12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Anth12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy coding is limited to creating a mod that can display parts coordinates. How I make the ModuleManager hook into the code I am not sure yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will take a look tomorrow at what I can do about the robotic drift. But that\u2019s a different\u00A0problem with bigger issues you have to deal with than the docking ports. But will see what I can do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T09:36:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, anything would be appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Poodmund","CreatedById":128643,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T10:34:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628325193\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nas for making it stock, you did read the opening post of this thread yeah?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure but it did also preface that statement with: \u0022Even though we still may release a minor patch here and there when needed...\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess it depends on how \u0027game-breaking\u0027 this issue is to be judged alongside others like persistent issues with the new alarm clock and ground anchors. I would hope to see a 1.12.3 at some point, not soon... but at some point, to give the game one last pat on the head.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"serdan","CreatedById":212918,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T11:10:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015493\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628260979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy point is that I can\u0027t see any commercial gains to be found for Take Two.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd as a commercial company they\u0027re obligated to seek the best economical solution for their owners.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou seem to be implying that they\u0027re legally prevented from doing the thing, That\u0027s silly. Requiring every single decision to be directly profitable would be insane. Open sourcing KSP would fall under \u0022community care/relations\u0022 which is something they already spend resources on. I\u0027ve already granted that it\u0027s not going to happen in reality, but it\u0027s absolutely something they \u003Cem\u003Ecould\u003C/em\u003E do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-07T11:10:50Z\u0022 title=\u002208/07/2021 11:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 7, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by serdan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakete","CreatedById":208801,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-07T11:48:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628325193\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nas for making it stock, you did read the opening post of this thread yeah?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but i\u0027d consider it a bugfix of the base game of ksp (\u0022here and there when needed\u0022) not a feature increment.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u00A0This means, the base game will not receive this as a bugfix?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, thank you for this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}